Each team races to pick which furry friend they'll re-create; the build must be life-size and able to move down the runway on a leash; the judges decide which team captures its dog's details the best.

The teams have 8 hours to create a pirate ship with a creative and cohesive story about its captain and the treasure they seek; the builders see how their creations hold up against the rest of the fleet.

The teams put an imaginative and dynamic twist on a summer camp theme by using power functions in their builds; the team with the most creative build blindly picks a prize and chooses another pair to receive what was left.

The contestants face off in a mini golf challenge; each team must transform a putting green into a playable mini golf hole, complete with obstacles that propel the ball and the story within the build.
The contestants build tall, strong and stylish castles using only regular bricks; a wrecking ball that ultimately decides the best execution of the challenge.
The remaining five teams fight to stay in the competition as they recreate iconic action-packed scenes from the Marvel Cinematic Universe.
Contestants are split into red and blue teams, where they compete to build a fast and fashionable race car.
The semi-finalists have 10 hours to build a fountain that uses water to create movement within their build; the 3 remaining teams get 24 hours to build their best creation possible.
Celebrity contestants Robin Thicke, Finesse Mitchell, Leslie Jordan and Cheryl Hiness build aerodynamic snowmobiles that will shoot off a snow jump.
The teams must build Santa a new sleigh that looks great and is tough enough to span across two chimneys filled with heavy holiday gifts.
The teams compete in two super-sized brick-building challenges; the winning team wins $20,000 for the charity of its choice.
The Falcon tasks the girls with investigating a string of robberies, and EDM band EliTe returns to Maywood Glen to perform a surprise concert
While Bry and Cam do some sleuthing at rehearsal, Adri and Ember create a gummy bear tracking device to help McKeyla find Maddy.
When a nightmare about Maddy leaves her reeling, McKeyla comes clean to the Falcon. Bry and Cam kill it at auditions and zero in on a new suspect
Ember's itching potions sends Grady to the nurse's office, where Adri and McKeyla question him. Bry discovers a mysterious clue in EliTe's music
McKeyla and Cam question Eli at his grandmother's house and follow him to the docks, where they learn about a diabolical plan
The girls arrive at the Maywood Glen art opening to search for Vex, but they have no idea what the elusive mastermind looks like

The four girls are demoted back to basics after they make a big deal out of saving the prince in the previous season. They are not allowed on any mission, even as a suspicious figure, Carson Lazarus, a criminal mastermind, is released from jail. Soon after, a figure who calls themselves "Retro" causes all technology to malfunction and glitch in Maywood Glen.

The Quail allows the four girls to figure out this case. McKeyla becomes increasingly suspicious of Kyle, but soon dismisses the idea of him being Retro just because he knew she liked fro-yo and was wearing a black hoodie, very much like the one Retro wears. They also suspect Devon D'Marco, a troublemaker, as she spray-paints handcuffs on a picture of a drone on a poster about the upcoming launch. All four girls except Bry, who has to babysit, make ways to get detention on Saturday with Devon. Bry runs a vocal recognition as Cam and Adri confront the troublemaker and McKeyla looks through her bag. Devon is proven to be innocent, just using the school's 3D printer to make skulls for her nana's birthday.
When a new point of evidence involving HAVOC points to Carson Lazarus, Adrienne and Bryden comb through her trash looking for clues.
Bryden analyzes Retro's voice, which gives the girls a new idea about his or her identity; and they need to use their wiles when a blackout threatens to delay their investigation.
Retro sets a trap for the girls, which causes the Quail to advise them to leave town.
When the girls learn about the Quail and McKeyla's super-secret plan to infilerate HAVOC, they enlist some new friends to help out with the mission.
In the Darklands, Jim becomes captured by Gunmar, but manages to save Clare's baby brother. Killahead bridge has been destroyed and the Trollhunters will stop at nothing to save Jim.
While Jim is trapped in the Dark World with Gunmar. The rest of the team builds a plan to rescue him, all while trying not to let the human world know Jim is missing.
When a new plan of action fails, the team finds a secret ability in Toby that helps the team in their search to help Jim.
On the hunt to free Jim the team finds that it may require the help of an old friend returned. Jim makes an alliance while in Gunmar's Prisons.
Hope springs from an unlikely source when Gunmar learns that Jim's friends are in the Darklands on a mission to bring him home.
Now out of the Darklands and readjusting to life in Arcadia, Jim and the team must face the consequences of their risky actions.
Multiple problems plague a frazzled Jim when his amulet goes on the fritz and Claire invites him to meet her parents at a family barbecue.
When a oozy creature shows up in Arcadia, Jim and the gang set out to find it - while playing parents to two sacks of flour for a school assignment.
In a revealing flashback episode, Otto and Dictatious vie for Gunmar's ear while an increasingly paranoid Steve finds an unlikely ally.
Señor Uhl sentences Jim and his friends to detention while Queen Usurna gathers evidence of a conspiracy. Draal comes face to face with Gunmar.
Facing serious accusations from the Tribunal, Jim gets the chance to see what his life would be like if he'd never found the amulet.
Jim stands trial for unleashing Gunmar while his friends race to clear his name. If convicted, he'll be sent to "The Deep," a dark realm of no return.
A monumental loss carries a warning from beyond the grave as Gunmar marches for the Heartstone Trollmarket. Can the team pull together to save the day?
epi_name: In the Hall of the Gumm-Gumm King

epi_desc: Simon, Theodore and Dave dry to prevent Alvin from going to the karate championship as they fear he might get hurt. Alvin and Theodore believe that Simon is dave's favorite so they try to prove that they can beat Simon at anything

After Simon fails a test , he decides to go on strike and that includes moving into a tree but the chipmunks and chippettes try to convince him to come back. Alvin fears that once Dave has read his report card , he won't get his new video game so he tries everything to make sure that Dave doesn't receive his report card.

Miss Croner leaves Theodore in charge of looking after her cats while she's gone out of town but he can't let his brothers or Dave find out / the chipettes think that the chipmunks are all addicted to one item they each like but they disagree so they do a test to see who can go the longest without touching their favorite items.

The chipmunks and chippetes think that alvin spoils shows but Alvin disagrees so they all bet that Alvin can't stop talking for 24 hours but he proves them wrong / Theodore wins a goldfish at a fair and loves it so much but Alvin and Simon thinks that he might be dead so go out to replace him.

Miss smiths pairs everyone in the class up to look after their own robot baby in order to experience a parents life but Alvin and Brittany struggle with the task. The coach decides to enroll Alvin , Simon and Theodore into a ballet class as their team can't beat Derek's team.

Theodore shows Alvin what life without Simon would be like but Alvin finds it quite boring. Theodore is winning the contest of the cutest chipmunks but Alvin tries everything he can think of to make sure he gets declared as the cutest chipmunk.
epi_name: Oh Brother Where Art Thou; The Wall

epi_desc: Theodore creates a handmade vest for Dave, but Dave's too embarrassed to wear it/ Theodore finds a winning lottery ticket and all his friends and family members try to influence what he spends the money on.

Someone has been painting all of the walls and it is up to the chipmunks and chippettes to find out who it is / Theodore finds a lucky clover and explains that lucky things happen to him when he's holding the lucky clover, everyone believes it except Alvin but afterwards he wants it.

Alvin gets a taste of his own medicine when he pulls one too many practical jokes on Simon. When Miss Croner finds termites have infested her home, she moves in with the chipmunks and drives everyone crazy.

When the boys accidentally break Dave's new flat-screen TV, they decide to become fugitives on the lam; Jeanette and Eleanor act as Sherlock Holmes and Watson when Theodore's teddy bear mysteriously disappears.

When the chipmunks get tired of Dave always telling them what to do , they decide to build a tree house in the backyard and live in it, when Simons experiment goes wrong, Alvin and Simon are magnetized to each other and struggle to cope with each other but they can't let anyone find out especially dave.

When Alvin, Simon and Theodore get stuck with miss Miller as a babysitter, they decide to get someone new but all of their choices aren't at all like they hoped they would be. When Alvin and miss smith get paired up they struggle to work together but in the end they found out that they're better working as a team.

When Dave gets temporary amnesia, the boys trick him into letting them skip school and go on a ski trip instead; Theodore becomes obsessed with cleanliness after a speaker at school talks to the class about the danger of germs.

Theodore tries to overcome his fear of sleepovers by spending the night at Kevin's house without Alvin or Simon. When Alvin sees every celebrity with their own personal bodyguard, he decides to train Theodore for the job.
epi_name: Theo's Big Night Out; The Bodyguard

epi_desc: With the trolls hiding out in Arcadia, AAARRRGGHH!!. goes undercover to see what Gunmar is up to. A potential rival brings out Jim's jealous side.
Toby gets caught in the crosshairs when a troll goes missing and the city cracks down on crime. An ancient voice refuses to be silenced.
Something strange is brewing at school, where the teachers are more agitated than usual. Claire's illness shows disturbing side effects.
A double date night becomes more lively than anyone anticipates when Morgana takes possession of Claire at dinner.
To free Claire from possession by Morgana, Stricklander is summoned to help, but Morgana has formidable ways to resist.

When Jim's mother's memories of the Troll world reemerge, she gathers Tobia and Claire's parents together to confront their children about their activities as the kids struggle to invent a cover story.
With the future of two worlds at stake, the team races to find Merlin's Tomb and the Staff of Avalon before Gunmar can get his hands on it.
A long-dormant ally shows Jim and his friends what really happened at the Battle of Killahead. Gunmar awakens Morgana, and Angor Rot plots his revenge.
Even while the Trollhunters gather components for Merlin for a spell, Jim's only chance to avoid being held back at school is to show around a pair of new and very strange exchange students.
As Gunmar hunts for the key to free Morgana, Merlin ruthlessly manipulates Jim into making a dramatic and irrevocable choice for what he considers the greater good.
A greatly changed Jim renews his Trollhunter training but struggles to accept his new reality. Gunmar and Morgana rally the troops for an attack.
The Eternal Night covers Arcadia in shadow, leading to a long-awaited showdown between Gunmar and the newly transformed Trollhunter.
An epic battle comes ahead in the darkness as Jim and his friends push back against Morgana. But without Merlin, how will they stop her?
After getting detention again, Alvin's convinced Dave will drive him to the desert and abandon him there.
Alvin and Theodore play a seemingly innocent game, which leads to unexpected consequences.
After the Chipmunks accidentally ruin Dave's new pavilion, they allow Miss Miller to take the fall.
Alvin's too short to ride an exhilarating new amusement park ride, so he devises a plan to sneak on after-hours.
Alvin's attempts to make money as an internet influencer almost drive a local toy store out of business.
The boys imaginations run wild as Dave disappears, when they find him they're convinced he's a zombie.

When the chipmunks find a stray dog, the boys do everything they can do hide it from Dave so they can keep it; Theodore buys an egg online in hopes it will hatch into a dragon, but Alvin and Simon do not believe his wish will come true.

When Alvin attempts to help the Mathletes stand up to bullies, they take their newfound confidence too far. After witnessing what appears to be a wallet theft commited by Alvin's new friend, a foreign student named Emil, Simon and Theodore decide to investigate in hopes of finding answers - and, perhaps, justice.
Alvin and Simon compete to determine who is a better magician. In order to pay off a fine, Alvin takes a job as a music teacher.
After watching a horror film involving hot wax, the boys fear Dave has been caught up in a similar story.

After Brittany overhears Alvin standing up for her, she begins to behave in a peculiar manner that leads Alvin to believe that she has been possessed by a body-snatcher. To land Simon a position on the school newspaper, Alvin and Theodore search for a groundbreaking story, discovering some interesting things about their teacher in the process.
Alvin goes to drastic measures to impress a girl he sees babysitting at the park. Alvin takes on numerous favors in order to do something special for Dave.

In Munk Man, Simon enters a superhero contest. The only thing that is a potential threat to him, lives with him. In Ride Along, Alvin's bicycle is stolen as is an officer's. Together they team up to catch the thief bringing hoots of laughter until the very end.

Alvin begs Dave to spend a weekend alone with him. Dave agrees and gets sucked into a series of adventures; a professional hypnotist accidentally hypnotizes Simon a few days before the Bellview Ultimate Trivia Tournament (the B.U.T.T.).
epi_name: Alvin's Wild Weekend/For Whom the Bell Tolls

epi_desc: Alvin gets a device that let's him listen in on everyone's conversations. When the kids' Halloween candy disappears, they're sure the culprit is "Switch Witch." Spooky adventure ensues as they try to track down their candy.
Alvin accidentally clones himself/A small lie turns into a giant one that everyone knows about
Brittany gets a Suck Toad stuck to her face/The Chipmunks think that Kevin has a crush on one of the Chipettes. The girls annoy him to get him to stop liking them
Simon accidentally sends a rude email to one of his teachers/Simon makes Theodore a No-Buddy to get him to stop saying yes to everything
Theodore accidentally gives a special music box to the principal of their school/Theodore's been mistakenly mailed off in a box. Alvin and Simon have to get him back.
Miss Smith quits her job and Alvin tries to get her back/The Chipettes post a video of a very scared Simon and Alvin on the internet
The Chipettes try to show the boys that girls can be superheroes too/Alvin is held back a year in school and tries to get Simon and Theodore to join him

Kevin fears his birthday party will be lame so Alvin decides to host a paintball party in his house. After learning about Bocarter's New Computer, The chipmunks decide to build a bigger and better one in order to beat him at his own game.
epi_name: It's My Party/Keeping Up with the Humphries

epi_desc: When a new boy band, "The Hipmunks, " tries to steal the spotlight, the Chipmunks are forced to compete in a battle of the bands. The Principal gives Alvin & Derek an ultimatum - if they fight, the school dance will be canceled.

When Brittany is hurt before a major school event, Jeanette fills in as the Principal's assistant. When Bocarter's father helps him with his class project, Alvin enlists Dave's help, locking the families in a heated competion.

After learning about The Knights of the Round Table, Theodore hopes to be a knight and comically struggles to do "good deeds." Alvin and Simon create a fake snake to help Dave get over his fear of snakes.

After Brittany and the girls release a video that goes viral, Alvin, Simon, and Theodore try to top it. Simon falls ill and asks Alvin and Theodore not to go see a new movie without him, but Alvin just can't resist.
Alvin borrows Simon's invisibility suit, but gets trapped when the zipper gets stuck; after Theodore makes a wish, the Chipmunks try to learn what it was, so they can make it come true.

Jeanette decides to plant a garden on the school grounds, but Bocarter manages to install vending machines instead. When Alvin finds a treasure map in Miss Croner's basement, the Chipmunks set off in search of lost treasure.

The chipmunks help an owner fix up his run-down summer camp and his broken relationship with his brother; Alvin believes that Theodore cursed him so that he can never lie again and cannot help himself from blabbing the truth.

Alvin and Brittany give wildly differing versions of why the fire alarm went off at the school to Miss Smith. Convinced a zombie invasion is imminent, Alvin and Theodore go all out in an attempt to protect their loved ones.
epi_name: He Said She Said/Attack of the Zombies

epi_desc: Body switching shenanigans ensue when Alvin and Jeanette are zapped with Simon's teleportation device./ When Theodore notices Cheesy is upset about not having a valentine, He pretends to be a girl on an online dating site to cheer him up.

Alvin and Brittany are convinced Simon has vanished back in time and go all out in an attempt to bring him back. A prank call by Alvin gets out of hand when the person on the other end of the line vows to track him down.
The Titans make their last stand against Trigon.
The Titans pick up another runaway stray. Hank and Dawn have adapted to a new life. Donna and Kory are on a stakeout.

With the re-emergence of Doctor Light, the old Titans reluctantly return to the Titans tower to strategise against their old enemy. But the secrets of the Titans' past threaten to tear apart this newly formed team from within.

Five years ago, the Titans and Garth aka Aqualad are growing into a tight-knit family. But their personal feelings start to bleed into their work, and with the arrival of a new villain, they begin to question their destiny as heroes.

With the team in disarray, Dick and the others vow to do everything in their power to save Jason's life. Gar's guilt over Jason's kidnapping complicates the mission, while Rachel's dark secret continues to gnaw at her.
A specimen of Project Cadmus escapes captivity and goes on the run with a loyal friend named Krypto.
As Dick sets out alone to track down Deathstroke, a familiar voice begins to haunt him - taunting him and attempting to guide him back to being the leader the Titans need.

After the murder of Aqualad, Dick, Donna, Dawn and Hank befriend Jericho Wilson, Deathstroke's son. Realizing that Slade's devotion to his son might be Deathstroke's only weakness, Dick is eager to use the information against his nemesis.
Dick's confession causes the Titans to go their separate ways. Hank and Dawn try to start a new life. Koriand'r encounters an unexpected threat. Gar tries to help Conner adjust.
Dick is sent to prison. Donna goes on a search for Rachel who has made some new friends. Titans Tower comes under attack by Mercy Graves.
With Dick still in prison and Gar under the microscope at Cadmus, the remaining Titans are called together to save their teammates.

While Hank is busy cage fighting after breaking up with Dawn, someone steals the Hawk suit. Donna and Dawn finds a way to rescue Gar from Cadmus facility. Rose reveals her secret to Jason. Dick escapes from prison to find Jericho.
The Titans battle Deathstroke and more.
When the Joker kills Jason, Dick returns to Gotham to see how Bruce is handling it.

Red Hood, emerges as a new crime lord and creates terrorist attacks in Gotham. Dick calls in the rest of the Titans for help. A showdown between Red Hood and the Titans leads to a shocking revelation.
Jason attaches a bomb to Hank's heart. The Titans have less than four hours to find the detonator.
Kory and Gar search for an explanation for Kory's mysterious visions. Meanwhile, Dick and Dr. Crane go on a road trip.
In flashback, we learn the story of how Jason became estranged from Batman, found his way to Dr. Crane, and the tragic turn of events that transformed him into Red Hood.
Crane enlists the help of lethal assassin Lady Vic, who has a troubled history with Dick and Barbara. Meanwhile, Kory and Gar bring Blackfire back to Wayne Manor.
Crane betrays Jason, and the Titans track Crane down.
As an emboldened Crane looks to filter his poison through Gotham's water system, Starfire, still plagued by visions, enlists Blackfire and Superboy's help, and Gar finally tracks down Jason.
While Rachel struggles for a chance to use her magic to resurrect Donna on Paradise Island, Tim Drake encounters Donna in the Underworld, and searches for a way back.
Crane turns Gotham against the Titans. Barbara takes a bold step and Rachel and Donna return as Gotham engulfs in chaos.
While Crane sets his ultimate sights on Nightwing, Gar and Rachel investigate Red Hood's place of rebirth, Donna and Tim reconnect in the real world, and Kory learns the truth about her past.
epi_name: The Call Is Coming from Inside the House

epi_desc: After Nightwing and Red Hood's battle, Rachel and Gar try to save their friend. Meanwhile, Jason questions his allegiance. With Barbara behind bars, Donna leads her own resistance operation, and Conner helps Blackfire recover her ship.
With Gotham once again at the mercy of Crane's terror, it's all hands on deck for the Titans as they infiltrate Wayne Manor and harness an ancient power that transcends life and death.
A favorite toy of Theodore's is lost on a rafting trip but then mysteriously shows up at the house...and it's alive.
Alvin wants Dave to take a DNA test to see if he's a famous explorer or king, but maybe it's a person much scarier.
Miss Croner attempts to help Theodore discover his true calling in life.
Jeanette is suddenly the clumsiest person on the planet. Is there something wrong with her - or her new glasses?
Theodore gets roped into doing Alvin's babysitting sitting job with a spoiled four year old.
Dave promises to take Alvin to a water park if he gets a good grade on his test, but then a crow steals it.
Kevin agrees to be Alvin's assistant to get closer to the music industry, but ends up running errands instead.
When Theodore discovers Alvin and Simon have a secret club, he promises not to tell anyone if they let him join.
When Alvin accuses Simon of being too safe, Simon agrees to do whatever crazy thing Alvin wants him to do.
When pirates show up at the house, the boys do all they can to protect a treasure chest that arrived for Dave.
A cute singing bird replaces Alvin in the band after Alvin makes too many demands as a performer.

A dangerous tidal wave washes all the fish up in the trees, which is also a big problem for the poison dart frogs who don't have enough puddles up in the trees for the tadpoles. Luckily, Tweak's new Gup-H is ready to help.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Poison Dart Frogs

epi_desc: The Octonauts are exploring Antarctica, when Shellington discovers strange microscopic creatures living under the ice.
The Octopod breaks down and Tweak and the crew search for a missing part on an abandoned prototype Octopod, but it's not completely abandoned.
As newborn baby sea turtles make their way to the ocean, the Octonauts must steer them clear a giant wave and hungry predators.
epi_name: Octonauts and the Baby Sea Turtles

epi_desc: Barnacles' nephews Ursa and Orso are going to get their Polar Scout Badges, when they spot three walrus pups on a drifting floe which is on a crash-course with 2 icebergs. The pups are lost and too hungry to swim. Will Captain Barnacles be able to save them and finally earn the Walrus Rescue Badge - the only one he hasn't got?
The Octonauts must get two mantis shrimp to stop fighting before their powerful claw strikes destroy the Octopod.

The Octonauts find a humpback whale who's all alone because his voice is different from the other humpbacks'. They have to help him because if nobody understands him, he won't find the way to the feeding ground.
Peso gets washed up by a storm on a mysterious rocky island and discovers a group of insects thought to be extinct called tree lobsters.
The Octonauts evacuate the creatures living around a reef before a large archway collapses, but one stubborn convict fish refuses to move from her burrow.
The Octonauts journey across a dangerous expanse of ice to help a penguin mother get back to her family.
Kwazii adopts a baby alligator, but when it escapes the Octopod, he must rescue the tiny creature from ocean currents and hungry predators.
While diving down to the Midnight Zone, the Octonauts are attacked by bomber worms, and are enlisted to rescue an injured member of their troop.
When a population of crawfish is stricken by a mysterious illness, the Octonauts race to find a cure.
Dashi teams up with her little sister, Koshi, to solve a mysterious disappearance in a kelp forest.
epi_name: The Octonauts and The Surfing Snails

epi_desc: Returning home from a mission along an African river, the Octonauts have trouble getting past a gang of large, territorial hippos.
epi_name: Octonauts and the Kelp Monster Mystery

epi_desc: The Octonauts wade through a swamp to find a lost flamingo chick before hungry predators do.
After Shellington crashes the Gup-D, he and Kwazii team up with a moray eel and grouper fish to pick up the pieces.
Tweak must help her friend Sandy the sea turtle escape a hungry tiger shark.
While exploring a dark and spooky cave, the Octonauts discover the fossil of a powerful, prehistoric fish - but it may be more than just a fossil.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Tiger Shark

epi_desc: When a mass of poisonous sea snakes get stranded on a beach, Peso and the Octonauts must somehow get them all back into the ocean.
The Octonauts struggle to save a pod of spinner dolphins who seem to be swimming in their sleep.
epi_name: Octonauts and the Yellow-Bellied Sea Snakes

epi_desc: Coconut Crisis: Kwazii and the Octonauts help their friends the coconut crabs discover who is stealing their coconuts. Sunfish: The Octonauts must help a giant sunfish who can't swim straight, before it hurts other sea creatures and itself.
The Great Swamp Search: The Octonauts journey to the Everglades to help Tweak's dad, Ranger Marsh, track down several invasive species - including a Burmese Python and her babies.

Coconut Crisis: Kwazii and the Octonauts help their friends the coconut crabs discover who is stealing their coconuts. Sunfish: The Octonauts must help a giant sunfish who can't swim straight, before it hurts other sea creatures and itself.
epi_name: Octonauts and the Great Swamp Search

epi_desc: Captain Barnacles, Kwazii, and Peso are visiting The Polar Scout Emergency Post run by Tracker - a young polar bear trained by Captain Barnacles. Suddenly they receive a signal for help from a deserted research station on the opposite side of the world. Whoever could have sent the signal, the Octonauts have to answer it.
Left to fend for herself in an empty house, Miranda tries to win back Uncle Jim and Patrick. Bethany sets out on a biblical adventure.
Uncle Jim and Miranda try to cash in on YouTube ads, only to end up at war with a taco chain. Bethany and her ex compete for Emily's affections.
Shocked to discover a young girl has been copying her act online, Miranda vows to take her rival down -- at a middle school talent show.
A trip to the hospital gives Uncle Jim a twisted new idea for his line of Miranda merchandise. Emily makes a selfless offer.
Miranda hits a major setback on the romantic front. Meanwhile, the new vibe between Bethany and Jim makes things awkward around the house.
While Miranda throws herself into building her theme park, Uncle Jim prepares a memorable first date, and a surprise visitor whisks Emily away.
As Miranda World opens to the public, guilty secrets and jealous rivalries threaten to spoil the fun.
Miranda finally gets a chance to make her mark on Broadway, but things don't go quite as expected. Money troubles force the family to get creative.
Wyatt and Rufus chase the Mothership back to 1918 France to try and rescue Lucy.
epi_name: The War to End All Wars

epi_desc: The team track Emma to 1955 South Carolina where a Rittenhouse sleeper agent is about to be activated.
The team head to 1941 Hollywood to track down another Rittenhouse sleeper agent.
While Wyatt sneaks away from the bunker to face an unbelievable truth, Lucy, Rufus and Flynn chase the Mothership to the 1692 Salem Witch Trials.
Wyatt and Rufus bring a 17-year-old boy to the present when a mission goes awry.
The team travel back to 1936 Texas to try and conserve 20th century pop culture, while Wyatt closes in on the Rittenhouse HQ.
epi_name: The King of the Delta Blues

epi_desc: The team land in 1919 New York to try and stop Rittenhouse from killing the suffragette movement.
The team travel back to 1981 Washington D.C. on the day that President Reagan was shot.
The team partners with Harriet Tubman to thwart Rittenhouse's plan to alter the outcome of the Civil War.
The team attempt to rescue Jiya.

With a little help from their future selves, Lucy and Wyatt, along with the rest of the team, journey to the California Gold Rush and the Korean War's Hungnam evacuation in a daring bid to save Rufus and stop Rittenhouse once and for all.
epi_name: The Miracle of Christmas Part I/II

epi_desc: Claire, back home in California, begins attending college, but is having difficulty adjusting when a mysterious death of a student during the orientation puts her back in the spotlight. In Japan, Hiro and Ando continue their quest to help people with abilities and go so much as to advertise themselves. Meanwhile, Angela fears Nathan/Syler will discover his true identity. Matt tries to settle down back in Los Angeles and raise his son and not worry about unexpected visitors. Elsewhere, Peter is using his ability for good when a mysterious carnival clan, led by Samuel Sullivan, arrives in town which could spell trouble for him and everyone else.

Samuel continues searching for the whereabouts of the soul of his brother. He begins to focus on Peter by using his ink-transparency powers to investigate Peter. Meanwhile, Claire deals with her secret being outed when Gretchen pressures her to tell the truth. But Noah, comes for a visit and immediately suspects that Gretchen knows about Clair's power. In Los Angeles, Matt Parkman continues dealing with Sylar's ghost taunting him and it hinders his latest case of trying to nail a suspected drug supplier. Also, a new 'hero' with powers is introduced; a young deaf woman named Emma, a dispatcher who works with Peter at the New York hospital, whom discovers that she can 'see and hear' sound breaks.

As Hiro's life continues to hang in the balance, he distracts himself with saving the lives of others. Meanwhile, Angela tries to help the new "Nathan" remember his past, at the risk of his remembering too much. Elsewhere, Tracy is determined to get her old job back, but soon realizes that she needs to make more of an impact.

Samuel prepares for new additions to his family, while Lydia warns him of the consequences. Claire discovers that her roommate Gretchen may have a hidden agenda. Meanwhile, Peter finds an unexpected way to connect with Emma, who would prefer to stay distant. Elsewhere, a different side of Sylar emerges as he desperately tries to remember the person he used to be.

Under Samuel's guidance, Sylar starts on a path to rediscover his true identity. Hiro helps Emma accept and understand the great possibilities that go along with having an ability. Meanwhile, Peter enlists HRG to help him find a healer who can save Hiro's life.

Matt goes to extreme measures to extinguish Sylar, who continues to torment him. Elsewhere, H.R.G. calls in a favor from Tracy to save a troubled young boy whose misfortunes resemble her own. While Claire and Gretchen are being hazed by their new sorority sisters, they realize pledging might not be their biggest problem.

When Hiro travels three years into the past, he has a second chance to save Charlie from the hands of Sylar. However, Samuel's presence serves to complicate Hiro's mission even further. Elsewhere, H.R.G.'s past with his Primatech partner is revealed.
epi_name: Chapter Seven 'Once Upon a Time in Texas'

epi_desc: Claire is determined to get to the bottom of the Sorority Rush attacks on her own, until H.R.G. intervenes only to realize he may be the source of her troubles. Meanwhile, Peter's new ability is a perfect fit for his job and gives him the opportunity to help Emma accept her new life. Elsewhere, Sylar's battle at gaining full control over Matt's body escalates -- with potentially dangerous implications at stake.
Samuel learns just how powerful he can become and takes dangerous measures to reach his full potential. Meanwhile, as Tracy begins to lose control of her ability, one of her own comes in harms way.

H.R.G. hosts a non-traditional Thanksgiving dinner by inviting Claire over at his apartment for dinner. But the dinner becomes more awkward and uncomfortable when Noah invites his former co-worker Lauren, while Noah's ex-wife, Sandra, also shows up with her newest beau, a younger man named Doug Douglas, whom like her also has a small dog fetish. Claire is also conflicted about where she wants to be, in which Noah invites over Gretchen to try to lift up her spirits. Meanwhile, the Petrelli family gets a surprise guest at their table when Sylar shows up having reclaimed Nathan's body and holds both Peter and Angela at his mercy. Elsewhere, Samuel continues to hold Hiro hostage as part of some grand master plan, as Lydia goes to Hiro in search of the truth about Samuel.

H.R.G. is greeted by some unexpected visitors and Samuel's grand plan begins to come to fruition. Meanwhile, Peter struggles to accept the truth and takes extreme measures to get what he wants. Elsewhere, Claire's journey leads her to an unexpected destination.

Samuel goes off and tries to bring Emma into the fold by manipulating her about how special her sight-of-sound powers are, while back at the Sullivan Brothers Carnival, Claire becomes more suspicious about Samuel's intentions and deals with not only Samuel's right hand, Replicating Man, Eli, but also the Puppet Master Eric Doyle. A delirium-stricken Hiro returns to Japan and tries to convince Ando in code-talk to help rescue Mohinder from a lunatic asylum in Florida where Hiro forcibly placed him for protection from Samuel.

Claire attends Nathan's funeral while Peter struggles with his grief in his own way by wanting to seek revenge. Meanwhile, Noah and Lauren interrogate a captured Edgar for information to where to find Samuel's carnival. Elsewhere, Sylar returns to Samuel's carnival where he and Lydia try to find a way to emotionally get inside the killer's head to make him see what is troubling him.

H.R.G. recruits Matt to help him take down Samuel, as they use his long-lost love, Vanessa, to lure him to them, but Samuel has his own plans for Vanessa in the works. Meanwhile, Hiro and Ando go to extreme lengths to save Dr. Suresh. Elsewhere, Peter's introduction of Emma to his mother brings forth visions of a very grim future.

Hiro's life hangs in the balance as his brain tumor worsens, prompting him to subconsciously deal with some of his past decisions. Meanwhile, Sylar pays Claire an unexpected visit to get answers as to why he isn't quite himself. Elsewhere, Samuel's plan to impress his long-lost love, Vanessa, takes a terrifying turn.

H.R.G. enacts his plan to take down the Carnival with the help of Lauren and Suresh. Sylar visits Matt looking to understand his desire to make a human connection, but Matt has a plan of his own. Meanwhile, Peter warns Emma of Samuel's intentions after his grim vision of the future.

Peter is forced to travel into Sylar's mind to ask for him to save Emma and the two of them find themselves in a limbo state-like deserted city where they try to find a way out. Meanwhile, Samuel tries to further manipulate Claire by showing the past of Noah's in image flashbacks showing his first wife, and the reasons why he came to work for The Company. Also, a wounded Lauren meets with Emma for medical treatment and to try to get her to listen about Samuel's nefarious plans.
Samuel's ultimate plan spells disaster for thousands.
Kwazii and Dashi become entangled in a strange deep-sea creature - a siphonophore - and when a geyser blasts it toward the surface, the Octonauts must stop its ascent before it fatally bursts.

Water Bears: The Octonauts venture into a dangerous red-hot lava tube to rescue a teeny tiny water bear, who doesn't seem to mind the heat at all! Barracudas: Shellington and the Vegimals mission to replant a mangrove forest is put in peril by a school of toothy barracudas.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Water Bears

epi_desc: Only Peso can save the day when a cone snail invades the Octopod and tranquilizes the crew one by one with its dangerous venom-filled harpoons.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Cone Snail

epi_desc: Humpback Whale: When a sardine swallows the key to a treasure chest, a humpback whale helps Kwazii track it down. Platypus: While rescuing river creatures after a storm, the Octonauts find a strange egg and come under attack by stinging platypuses.
When a floating garbage patch endangers a flock of pelicans and other sea creatures, the Octonauts and the birds work together to clean it up.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Humpback Whales

epi_desc: The Octonauts must stop a huge herd of sea pigs before they march blindly into the Mariana Trench - the deepest point on earth.
As Tweak tests the Gup-X deep down in the Midnight Zone, a yeti crab cuts a vital electrical wire in the ship and cuts off all power, endangering itself and the Octonauts.
Shellington and the Vegimals are on a mission to replant a mangrove forest that is put in peril by a school of toothy barracudas.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Yeti Crab

epi_desc: While rescuing river creatures after a storm, the octonauts find a strange egg.
When Kwazii gets lost at sea aboard the tiny octo-ski, he meets a flotilla of even tinier sea skaters, the only insects of the ocean.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Duck-Billed Platypus

epi_desc: The Octonauts attempt to keep the peace amongst a trio of mudskippers whose home has been flooded.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Sea Skaters

epi_desc: When Peso's patient, a remora fish, mysteriously disappears, the Octonauts enlist a unique undersea detective - a harbour seal.
An enormous lion's mane jellyfish gets its amazingly long tentacles tangled in the Octopod's engine whilst Tweak is working on it and causes havoc.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Harbor Seal

epi_desc: Red Rock Crabs: When Shellington and the crew try to gather some skittish crabs who have drifted away from home, they get help from some old friends. Sea Pigs: The Octonauts must stop a huge herd of sea pigs before they march blindly into the Mariana Trench - the deepest point on earth!
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Lion's Mane Jellyfish

epi_desc: Examining a sick sea sponge, Peso is surprised to discover that all sorts of creatures live inside it, treating it like a hotel, a behaviour known as commensalism.

Mudskippers: The Octonauts attempt to keep the peace amongst a trio of mudskippers whose home has been flooded. Immortal Jellyfish: Shellington and the Octonauts try to track an unusual creature: a jellyfish that can transform from old to young repeatedly - and live forever!
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Sea Sponge

epi_desc: Urchin Invasion: The Octonauts head to the kelp forest to visit Shellington's sister, Pearl, and her newborn son Periwinkle - only to find the forest endangered by an infestation of kelp-eating urchins! Lionsmane Jelly: A lionsmane jellyfish gets its long and stingy tentacles tangled in the bubble engine, unintentionally flooding the Octopod and causing havoc.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Immortal Jellyfish

epi_desc: Pelicans: When a floating garbage patch endangers a flock of pelicans and other sea creatures, the Octonauts and the birds work together to clean it up. Hammerhead Sharks: The Octonauts study a group of baby hammerhead sharks, as they hunt on their own for the first time and poke their noses into trouble.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Urchin Invasion

epi_desc: Sea Sponge: A sea sponge that houses other sea creatures in its pores suffers from a mysterious illness and Peso must figure out the cause. Loggerhead Sea Turtle: When an underwater tremor separates the Gup-X and its crew, Barnacles seeks guidance from a mysterious sea turtle.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Hammerhead Sharks

epi_desc: When the Octopod goes in for repairs the Octonauts take a vacation, and Peso accompanies Barnacles to help his sister and her new polar cubs learn to navigate the harsh conditions of the frozen arctic.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Loggerhead Turtle

epi_desc: Tweak has designed a brand-new Deep Sea Station to study the deepest, darkest reaches of the ocean, but the Octonauts face multiple challenges: from getting it down there, to the extreme environment and strange, prehistoric creatures that greet them once they arrive.
epi_name: The Octonauts and the Great Arctic Adventure

epi_desc: With her brave dog at her side, Dora races on her scooter to the Big River so they can rescue Boots.
epi_name: Dora and Perrito to the Rescue

epi_desc: Dora, Boots, Benny and a stroller full of rambunctious puppies rush to save their puppy friend, Little Boots, before he wakes up a bear.

Dora and Boots are making a Shape Train in his Boots' sticker book, but when the train goes rolling down the track without Círculo the steering wheel, they need your help to catch it before it gets to Big Turn!
Dora is reading a book of nursery rhymes to Abuela's kitty, Lucky. Lucky loves the one about the three little kittens who ring the bells on their mittens as they dance and sing!
Dora and Boots put on their roller skates and take off on a skating adventure to stand up to a bully named Big Wheeler and open Skate Park for everyone.
Dora, Boots and Verde the clean-up truck need your help on an adventure to clear up a flood at Party Park in time for Verde's birthday party! ¡Vámonos!
After helping Sparky the horse feel better, Dora goes on one more ride with him before bringing him back to the barn. Help them watch out for Swiper, prickly bushes and falling rocks!
It's time for the Rainforest Talent Show, but first Dora and Boots have to rescue Benny so he can tell his jokes in the show.
Dora and Diego travel back to prehistoric times and go on a dinosaur adventure to find Baby Jaguar and bring him home to his birthday party.
epi_name: Dora and Diego in the Time of Dinosaurs

epi_desc: The Ice Witch has taken everyone's ice skates in the Snowy Forest and Dora must skate against her to get them back.
Dora, Boots, and Abuela are exploring the rainforest looking for the secret door to Adventure Forest! It's a magical forest amusement park that Abuela used to go to when she was a little girl!
While Dora's kitties run through a magic mirror, Dora becomes Dora in Wonderland! Join her and Boots on a double-length adventure through the magical, mixed-up world of Wonderland.
Dora takes a Magic Cape back to the Prince's Castle so she can break the spell that turned the Prince into a lion.
Dora travels to Brazil to play in the Big Cup Soccer Tournament, and if her team can beat the Monsters, they'll win the big cup.
When all of the magic in Fairytale Land starts to vanish, Dora and Boots must get magical water from the center of Sparkling Lake, which is hidden deep in the Never-to-be-Seen-Again Forest.
Dora and Boots rush to take Dora's Night Light to the Library before it gets too dark for the little chickens' special story time.
Dora and Boots need to help the Fairy Godmother fix her magic wand, so she can get her puppy back!
Dora, Boots, and Diego set out to rescue their bunny, turtle and butterfly animalito friends and bring them back home to their Copal Tree.
Dora and Boots try to keep a very sleepy Baby Bear awake long enough to get her home for her winter nap.
epi_name: Dora and the Very Sleepy Bear

epi_desc: Dora and Boots are waiting for a visit from the Hip-Hop-Bunny, who's bringing all the Easter Eggs for the big Egg Hunt! But when Swiper swipes the Hip-Hop-Bunny's basket, Dora and Boots need your help on an adventure.

Join Dora for a Father's Day adventure! When the Little Kite she makes for Papi gets blown away in the wind, she'll need your help taking a hovercraft and a go-cart to catch Little Kite before she goes out over the ocean!

Dive into adventure with Mermaid Dora and Sea Monkey Boots to help their mermaid friend Maribel get back to her Mami in Mermaid Cove! Plus rescue castaway Benny from Coconut Island and join Dora on a magical moonlight adventure through a storybook world!

Get ready for two REWARDING ribbon adventures! First, help Dora get to the Big Gymnastics Show to start it off with her special rainbow ribbon dance, and then, saddle up with Pinto the Pony to win a blue ribbon at the Big Horse Show! Â¡FantÃ¡stico!
Dora and her friend, Emma are off on a science-filled journey to take their pretend volcano to the Green Power Science Fair.
One night, while taking care of Abuela's 3 kitties, Dora awakens to find that Lucky has chased a ball of string right into a storybook world! Help her find him on a magical moonlight adventure!

Dora has a big surprise for Perrito on Surprise Hill, but Swiper's trying to get there first to swipe it! Join Dora, Boots, and Perrito for an animal-filled adventure with help from lots of friends and their playful pets too!
Dora and her cousin Diego are on their way to a big surprise. It's Boots and Baby Jaguar's Amazing Animal Circus!
epi_name: Dora and Diego's Amazing Animal Circus Adventure

epi_desc: Dora and Boots are getting ready for a big beach picnic with their friends, but when Benny gets stranded on Coconut Island, he'll need rescuing from Dora, Boots and YOU!
Dora and Boots take Baby Bongo on a musical adventure as they race to the Big Music Show in time for Baby Bongo's first performance.
At Finland's Kylmakoski prison, Raphael meets violent offenders in the general population wing and bonds with the inmates, while a newcomer is attacked.
Surrounded by many inmates who struggle with crystal meth addiction, Raphael enters the Pilsen prison and discovers that some habits are hard to break.
epi_name: Czech Republic: The Crystal Meth Prison

epi_desc: Raphael gets a rare look inside Bangli prison, where drug offenders are forced to join a rehabilitation program and isolation is used as punishment.
At the Rove maximum security prison, many of inmates serve time for sexual offenses while navigating grim conditions and extremely limited resources.
Mohammad Alai Jr tests a battle-eager Yuujirou Hanma. Even though he's been poisoned, Kaiou Retsu enters Baki Hanma into the Great Chinese Tournament in China.
Baki engages with the best poison hand user of China. But there is a twist. The recovery is complete.
Kaiou Kaku is 121 years older than his opponent, but the legendary reigning champion doesn't hesitate to face Kaiou Samwan in the arena.
After a few fights, the tables turned against the hosts. Teams are formed to finish the tournament. Chinese vs US-Japan allies.
Oliva is up against a peculiar technique user. Mr. Unchained experiences the reluctant style of fighting.
The Bailin Temple legend, Retsu is in the ring against a sly and tricky Jaku.
The legendary Sea Emperor has to face the Strongest creature on Earth, the Ogre in the final match of the tournament.
He who wins this match will be the strongest man on earth. The battle intensifies. The best martial artist vs the strongest.
Mohammed Alai Jr. seeks the strongest underground fighters in Japan and challenges them to fight.
Mohammed Alai Jr. faces a strong opponent who pushed him to the furthest edge. His willpower alone is supporting him.
A past legend comes to visit Alai Jr. and challenges him. Jr. is determined to fight Baki.
Baki faces Mohammed Alai Jr in the presence of their fathers. The underground fight is not all that is happening in front of the spectators.
The Ogre accepts his son's challenge and Inspector Sonoda goes out to know about the death row inmates in different facilities. He discovers a shocking fact about all of them.
Raphael Rowe travels to Moldova and locks himself up in penitentiary number 17, a heavily guarded prison with hundreds of prisoners in for life.
The Central Jail of Nicosia in Cyprus has undergone radical transformation over the years. But are these changes for the better?
At Zenica prison at Bosnia and Herzegovina, Raphael Rowe finds himself trapped with inmates ranging from organized crime bosses to ruthless killers.
Raphael Rowe investigates one of Greece's most overcrowded maximum-security prisons, overflowing with some of the country's most dangerous offenders.
At Brandvlei correction Centre in South Africa nearly all of the Convicts in prison belong to dangerous gangs known for stabbings.
epi_name: South Africa: The Number Gangs Prison

epi_desc: Once again, Raphael Rowe volunteers to go behind bars, this time in the Philippines at Manila City jail, one of the world's most overcrowded prisons.
epi_name: Philippines: The War on Drugs Prison

epi_desc: Greenland's Nuuk maximum security prison houses extremely dangerous prisoners, many of whom grew up alongside the guards now watching over them.
Raphael Rowe spends a week behind bars at Tacumbu prison in Paraguay, where inmates scrounge in the trash in order to pay their own way.
epi_name: Paraguay: The Most Dangerous Prison on Earth

epi_desc: Schwalmstadt, a 12th-century fortress surrounded by a moat, houses some of Germany's worst offenders, many of whom attend intense therapy sessions.
The tropical island of Mauritius is home to Melrose maximum security prison, where even the smallest infraction is met with extreme punishment.
An unnerved Rowe contends with aggressive cellmates at Maseru prison, where a high number of inmates are behind bars for rape.
Though he's no stranger to life behind bars, Raphael Rowe concedes that Costa Rica's La Reforma Prison is certainly among the most intimidating.
epi_name: Costa Rica: Prison on a Knife-Edge

epi_desc: While spending a week inside Bogota's fortress-like prison, Raphael Rowe must negotiate the oppressive atmosphere and deal with an ominous threat.
Raphael Rowe spends a week at a maximum security prison in Craiova, Romania, where he inmates include rapists, murderers and contract killers.
Norway wants to be the model prison. Instead of humiliation they treat you with kindness and compassion. Raul felt weird. Eventually the goal is to have the inmate be a perfect citizen.
A tribute to the '69 Dodge Charger Daytona gives newbies Brian and Jake a chance to prove their skills. Shawn's plan could snare a Ferrari 458 Italia.
A client requests an uncommon modification to a Tesla. They transform the Tesla into a Dodge and take it to a racetrack.
Shawn needs to sell a unique hot rod. Gotham Garage considers a project that may lead to profitable opportunities.
Crew air concerns over garage direction. Harley Dyna gets sleek new look. Mark works on novelty vehicle request.
Tony has $10K budget to restore dual-cab bricknose truck. He transforms it into a rat rod. Meanwhile, Mark and Shawn consider buying a Ferrari 360 Spider, but it has issues.
While waiting on the Ferrari news, the team turns an old pontoon boat into a floating party bus; a 1969 Chevelle gets a 21st-century update.
Mark risks his shop's finances on restoring a classic car. A customer returns to see the finished $60k restoration.
Ferrari undergoes risky modifications at Gotham shop. Car unveiled at party, determining shop's fate.
Investigative journalist Raphael Rowe spends a few days -- both as a guard and a prisoner -- inside Brazil's gang-filled Porto Velho Penitentiary.
Raphael Rowe visits the short-staffed Bomana Prison in Papua New Guinea, where near-constant food shortages keep the facility on the brink of chaos.
epi_name: Ukraine: The Prison in a War Zone

epi_desc: Raphael Rowe visits the short-staffed Bomana Prison in Papua New Guinea, where near-constant food shortages keep the facility on the brink of chaos.
epi_name: Papua New Guinea: The Breakout Prison

epi_desc: In Belize Central Prison, the inmates are told that rehabilitation comes through God. Raphael Rowe investigates if this evangelical approach works.
epi_name: Belize: The Prison That Found God

epi_desc: When a group from the Shell is invited to the Offshore, Joanna sees a chance for revenge. But soon she becomes distracted by unsettling memories.
After a surprise announcement from André, Michele begins training Xavier for a different kind of mission. Verõnica escorts Joana to a secret meeting.
As the group prepares to raid the RTC, Glória makes a fateful deal, Michele finds herself trapped, and Rafael reconnects with a familiar face.
Forced to resort to plan B, Joana and the others flee to an underground hideout, where Natália wrestles with a difficult decision.
As panic sweeps through the Offshore, Marcela scrambles to restore order, and Marco discovers his mother isn't the only family member on the island.
With tensions rising and rumors spreading fast, André locks down the Process building and presents four candidates with a harrowing final test.
Waking up to a new reality, the Inland and Offshore factions inch closer to the brink of war -- until a long-lost artifact offers a ray of hope.
A hospital patient set to get his tonsils removed, but fears the cursed hospital may have other plans that include amputating his foot.

A curious boy accompanies his mother to his deceased grandfather's home. After trying on his grandfather's glasses, he realizes they may not be alone in the house as a sinister spirit seems to be lurking about.
Alice is lured back into her old Victorian house for one more night.
Nate finds himself in trouble when he imagines his sister being punished for her bullying.
Karen and Zach's family moves to the same farm that once belonged to evil old man Palmer and his creatures.
Ted's obsession with online auctions threatens more than just his money stash.
Sam's parents' latest impulse buy takes them on a road tip to an unfamiliar area.
Greg looks to the legends of his Irish heritage to turn his bad luck around.
While on a hike in the woods, strange things begin to happen to Melvin's family.
A mysterious gifts enters the home of Missy and her family, and there will be no rest for the merry.
Just as Joana tours Michele's new desert sanctuary, known as the Shell, a massive sandstorm moves in and wreaks havoc.
While the residents of the Shell prepare for the next stage of the Selection, Joana summons allies from the Cause and reveals her master plan.
Forced to stand in for Michele on the next test, Elisa finds herself longing for the Offshore. Artur struggles to hide his condition from Rafael.
With supplies dwindling, Michele hurries to cut the Shell's remaining population in half. In flashbacks, the Founding Couple face an agonizing dilemma.
Glória whips up support for her campaign, leading to chaos at the Shell. Marco resorts to desperate measures when he runs out of food for his son.
With the Offshore contingent on the way, the Shell's new residents scour the desert for the fugitives. Elisa grapples with painful memories.
While Joana and Rafael race to find proof of the sabotage, Michele faces an angry crowd, and new details emerge about Glória's time in the Process.
The truth about the sabotage finally comes to light as Marcela prepares to take over the Shell -- and carry out a secret personal mission.
Laura returns home which quickly creates problems for Valerie.

A sudden death has Val questioning her life choices, while Alex struggles with Jeff's intrusion in his family. Laura finds it difficult to balance her relationship with her new career and Leon and Leia receive unexpected news.

The realities of Valerie's impulsive decision begin to take hold as Laura endures the fallout from her fight with Tathiana. Alex navigates the bizarre world of virtual dating and makes a surprising connection.

Alex embarks on a psychedelic getaway only to encounter anunpleasant figure from his past, while Valerie runs into an old flame during a night out with John. Laura maneuvers a new career opportunity around an inscrutable boss.

During Alex's Last Super Bowl party gone awry, Valerie introduces John to the gang as Alex processes Rae's decision to move out. Laura has a chance run-in with Tathiana. And Leon and Leia are at an impasse after Leia's recent revelation.

Following a day of misguided decisions, Alex, Valerie, and Laura begin their overdue pilgrimage to Dawn's. But when their road trip takes an accidental turn, each faces an obstacle that tests their willpower in different ways.

Alex's "first date" with Rae goes less smoothly than planned, while a stubborn John tries Val's patience. Laura returns to Tathiana with a newfound resolve, and Leon and Leia begin the process of mediation.
Alex and Valerie grapple with an unexpected death in the family, and put momentous life decisions on hold to go on a double date. Laura finds clarity in her love life.
While watching the 1957 sci-fi B-movie "I Was a Teenage Tick", John is sucked into the world of the film.
Will John find a way home, or will he be trapped in a surreal horror movie world forever? He has to be resourceful to escape his fate.
Norman is assigned to collect insects for a class assignment, and he soon discovers that he has power over these insects and can make them do what he says.
While on his first flight, Josh learns that the old women sitting near him is actually the Grim Reaper.
Siblings enter into a pumpkin patch that is owned by a murderous farmer who kidnaps kids, removes their head, and switches the heads with the pumpkins in his garden.
When comic book fan Corey gets hold of his favourite illustrator's paintbrushes, he finds art beginning to mix with reality.
Alex is quite enjoying being home alone, sick, until strange things start happening around the house.
Willie and Drake want to replace their school mascot, Big Yellow, with a wolf, but Big Yellow doesn't like their idea.
A girl who doesn't respect her mother is given various animal figurines to teach her a lesson she won't soon forget.
After moving into a new home, a brother and sister discover that many years ago, an abusive man lived there with his family.
Young Jenny's acre is beset with bugs and birds, so, going against family advice, she accepts a scarecrow from a mysterious, intellectual stranger dressed in black.
During a stay at a sleepaway camp, two girls are harassed by a sadistic spider-like boogeyman that haunts their dreams, not to mention a bully, Meg, who makes things even worse.
A sorcerer's apprentice and an indentured maid, both orphans with no freedom, begin a quest to seek out the spiteful witch who was exiled after betraying her former master.
After tricking their cruel master sorcerer, the master's apprentice and maid both learn that the witch who has helped them is just as evil as he is, if not worse.
During the school's Hansel and Gretel play, the teenagers performing it discover that it might be cursed.
Being the new kid in school isn't easy, but for Seth, it's worse. Odd things begin happening around him on a trip to a museum.
A very nice but unpopular teenage girl gets into teen modeling and finds herself becoming more beautiful superficially, but really ugly personality-wise.
When a young girl rescues a mysterious doll from neighbourhood bullies, she fixes it but it soon becomes clear that the doll is no ordinary plaything.
With days to go before the next Process, Joana tries to prove herself to the leader of the Cause, and Michele faces an ultimatum from Ezequiel.
As Rafael races to score a spot on the Inland squad, flashbacks recap his first year in the Offshore. Fernando reluctantly coaches Process hopefuls.
Desperate to protect Glória, Fernando realizes there's another way to stop the Process. Michele and Rafael separately try to contact the Cause.
Ivana and Joana subject their captives to grueling interrogations to find out who's telling the truth. Marcela reaches out to an Inlander for help.
Michele and the others discover another side to Ezequiel as he retraces his turbulent journey from Process No. 80 to the present.
As the hunt for Cause members heats up, Glória wrestles with nagging doubts, Michele and Joana search for the bomb, and Fernando makes a defiant move.
Fernando finds an unlikely new ally. Michele undergoes a mysterious procedure. A crisis leaves Rafael torn between Elisa and his mission.
Joana finds herself at the mercy of a figure from her past, Michele is led to a remote hiding place, and Marcela receives an unexpected invitation.
While Rafael, Fernando and Joana forge ahead with their plan, Michele discovers a shocking secret about the Offshore's past.
Last-minute setbacks force Fernando and Joana to improvise. As chaos erupts on the day of the Process, Michele concocts a plan of her own.
When a brother and sister visit their grandpa at his retirement community, they soon discover why its residents only come out at night.
A grandpa must protect and save his grandchildren from the bloodthirsty residents of his retirement community.
When Lex rats out his friends for egging the house of a mysterious cat lady, her cats begin to follow him and take interest in his increasingly itchy arm cast.
Chi has no friends and lacks confidence. While spending a reluctant weekend at a school-mates house, Chi must face his fears and save newfound friends.
Eve feels like an outsider in her family, almost completely ignored since her new baby brother was born. But finds comfort in a new friend she meets in the woods behind her house.

Shortly after a 10 year-old boy who recently moved into a neighborhood meets a woman who gives him a space helmet with 2 way radio, he starts to hear voices from "Spaceman One" Even though there's no batteries in the helmet.

Georgia always looks forward to receiving her dad's international postcards in the mail. But on this trip around the world, it appears as though someone, or something, seems to be following him. Guest starring Mackenzie Foy.
Shawn has a problem - his best friend and his brother can't stand each other. But the real problem is the friend is imaginary and just refuses to leave.
12-year-old Bobby has a new roommate -- a French exchange student who rapidly shows signs of being an alien -- with plans for Earth.
After Jeremy and Bonnie's grandmother passes away, they travel to Russia to lay her ashes to rest and uncover a secret from her past. Guest starring Dylan Schmid and Kacey Rohl.
Jeremy must use his grandmother's secret to save her village, and his sister, from an evil creature. Guest starring Dylan Schmid and Kacey Rohl.

When Becky becomes obsessed with an enchanted painting, she starts recreating her own life to be identical to the girl in the painting's, but realizes that nothing is ever as perfect as it seems. Guest starring Bailee Madison.

Digital tech addicts Chelsea and Jeremy are annoyed, to say the least, about having to get dragged along on vacation with their mundane parents. But when they come upon a hotel with a sinister secret, will the family fall apart forever?

Maggie is madly in love with the dreamy and popular Brendan and will do anything to get him to notice her. So when Cupid shows up offering to help, she asks him to double his usual dosage, resulting in a frightful attraction.
A group of kids hold a ritual in their attic to contact a ghost and unfortunately, it becomes much more than just a kid's game.

An unlikely group of high-school students spend the afternoon together in detention, where strange things start appearing. Eventually they must each face the truth of why they're really in detention or else be stuck in school forever.
Kelly begins to notice that her brother has been acting strangely. As their dysfunctional family takes a toll on his psyche, he finds solace in a sinister fun-house run by a creepy carny.

After receiving a set of worry dolls from her workaholic parents, Jodanna and her brother Max start encountering strange events around their house. Unable to get her parents attention, Jodanna realizes that whatever she worries about becomes a reality.
Three kids think they're taking a shortcut through the woods, but a strange force is stalking them and the woods themselves take on a life of their own.
When the old tree in Ethan's backyard is cut down, the spirit of a vengeful convict who was hung on its branches returns.
A boy gets a new guitar and it can make him a rock star, but it may cost him his soul.
Jake Skinner is back, being his bad self.
Philip has his own robot, and while that sounds cool, it has certain... drawbacks.
Jason, a problem child, is given one more chance. Then he's accidentally given a monster.
When Logan and his dad are tasked with cleaning out his grandfather's house, the ghosts of secrets long past come back to haunt them.
Jared tries to turn off an annoying kids show, but shutting off the TV isn't doing the trick.
In the wake of Charles' death, Alex and Valerie adjust to their new lives apart. Laura schemes to remove her tattoo. Dawn makes an unexpected announcement.
After the memorial for their father, Alex and Valerie discuss where to bury their father's ashes while spending one last night roaming the streets of the neighborhood where they grew up.
epi_name: Things to Do in Burbank When You're Dead

epi_desc: Valerie enlists Leon's aide when she needs help in accepting delivery of a new dining room table. Laura participates in a sex study. Alex pitches his new business idea to investors.
Valerie goes shopping to update her wardrobe before her first storytelling class. Alex reconnects with Emmy. Laura starts a new exciting job collecting signatures for a new ballot proposition.

A date inspires Alex to consider his future. Valerie's fling with her classmate doesn't go quite the way she wants it to go. A woman gives Laura some troubling information about the ballot proposition she is collecting signatures for.

Alex once again faces the demands of working full-time. Valerie catches up with Jennifer and learns an intriguing secret about Jack. While interning for a new environmental group, Laura goes door-to-door collecting signatures.
Rae's discovery of a rat in the bathroom sparks a hunt through Alex's house. Leon and Leia's relationship escalates.
Alex makes an unlikely friend at work while trying to unearth the identity of Valerie's brother. Laura's relationship with Casey intensifies. Valerie finds her new arrangement with Jack maddening.

Valerie and Jack drive to Fresno to meet Valerie's half-brother. Laura considers whether to speak at a town council meeting. Alex's plan to impress a co-worker backfires when his house is taken over by a YouTube celebrity's photo shoot.
Alex searches for answers after losing his sexual prowess. Valerie obsesses over Jack's choices while planning a double date with Alex and Judy. Laura finds herself lost after a hard goodbye.
Valerie is roped into being a bridesmaid for a wedding she thinks is ridiculous. Alex and Judy revel in their new romance. Laura raises money for a move to Sacramento.
It's 1999. A young Valerie and Alex prepare for an unexpected pregnancy. In present day, Laura visits Casey in Sacramento and Valerie's relationship with Jack reaches a breaking point.
Valerie tries to repair her relationship with Laura while confronting resentments she harbors towards Dawn. Alex resolves to embark on an epic camping trip-but is epically derailed.
Alex's troubling new obsession leads Valerie to take matters into her own hands. Laura investigates switching high schools.
Alex embraces his new role as Laura's teacher but his methods are questionable. Valerie reaches out to old friends and makes an unsettling discovery.

Valerie tries to take her friendship with fellow therapist Jennifer to the next level. Alex considers an offer from a venture capitalist to keep Snooger from going under. Laura considers joining a homeschool study group.

Alex hosts a dinner for his new business partner Jordan, only to be confronted with someone from his past. Valerie joins Jennifer for Game Night with her friends. Laura gets to know one of the girls from her home school group.
Valerie considers her fertility options after a visit with her doctor. Alex reexamines a relationship with an ex-girlfriend. Laura and Aubrey bond over a secret.

Valerie agrees to be set up with Jennifer's friend Harry, but her mind is on someone else. Alex tries to impress Sarah with an engagement gift. Laura's friendship with Aubrey intensifies when things get personal.
Valerie finds herself with a choice between two very different men. Alex's relationship with a young coworker attracts attention. Laura and Aubrey make Spencer an offer he can't refuse.

Alex's personal and professional lives collide after Sarah and Jordan's engagement party. Valerie rethinks her decisions after being stood up. Laura's interest in Spencer complicates things with Aubrey.
Alex goes to war with Jordan over the future of Snooger. Valerie's trip out of town with Jack is overshadowed by drama at home. Laura's plan to visit Spencer in the hospital hits a roadblock.
Valerie and Jack indulge their fantasies at a hotel. Alex adjusts to his new life with Sarah. Laura and Spencer screen a series of teen romance films.
Valerie is forced to spend time with Drew and their accountant. Alex seeks help from a therapist. Laura assists Spencer with some difficult decisions.
Alex plans a 40th birthday for Valerie and makes a new friend. Valerie and Drew revisit a special place from their past. Laura makes a permanent decision regarding Spencer.
Dad comes to the house so he can die in peace. Valerie thinks about going back to Drew again. Alex tries to do what is best and Laura struggles with her decision to leave her "boyfriend".
Eager to make some cash, the crew gets to work on two projects: creating a rat rod from scratch and making a customer's Elite Laser 917 race-worthy.
Shawn pitches the Gotham crew on an upgrade-and-trade deal involving a 1957 Chevy. Also on the agenda: an epic automotive mash-up.
Mark and Shawn visit a salvage yard with hopes of trading in their newly completed '57 Chevy for some good old-fashioned Detroit iron.
After losing money on a build, the Gotham crew gets back to doing what they do best by turning a 1954 Army ambulance into a blinged-out party bus.
A broker representing a wealthy client shows interest in the yet-to-be-sold concept car combo. Later, Caveman pitches the crew on a project for a pal.
The Gotham Garage crew sets out to turn a Lincoln Zephyr that's seen better days into something truly special for a high-profile car show.
While the crew cranks on the Zephyr, Shawn pitches Mark on a deal involving a 1957 Kenworth big rig, just like the one Mark's dad used to drive.
epi_name: Go Big Rig or Go Home

epi_desc: Pumped at the opportunity to be on the cover of a Speedway catalog, Mark and company pull out all the stops to get the Zephyr ready for its closeup.
Business is booming for the Gotham crew, thanks to their recent recognition; tackling turning a 1933 Ford replica into an art deco Delahaye.
To finance a costly job redo, the crew works on an El Camino cash car for a very demanding client while overhauling an International Harvester Scout.
With everyone desperate for cash, Tony sees opportunity in a sentimental build; Shawn has a tough time finding a buyer for Mark's woody iteration.
After some creative deal making, Shawn frets over Mark's hot take on a Bel Air; an academic achievement leads to a school bus upgrade for Caveman.
As Mark presses to finish the hot tub car and fulfill a commitment to some friends, Shawn persuades him to upgrade a vintage Ford pickup as insurance.
Mark harbors a lowrider vision for a vintage Impala, aimed at financing his high-concept car; the plans get very elaborate.
Mark's Hayabusa hopes are tied to his take on a Prius; Shawn tries to generate buzz ahead of an auction, but a real-world roadblock gets in his way.
The crew gets creative when social distancing hurts their hopes for a big payday; Mark's high price demands may end up costing them even more.
The new shop is open for business; the Gotham crew upgrades a 1953 Buick Special and then attempts to convert a gas engine to electric.
After enduring a setback, the crew focuses on flipping a souped-up motorcycle for some money and finding their next great trade-up car.
As Shawn tries to fix a deal gone bad, he pushes Mark to take on a sentimental project; the garage gets a chance to impress a splashy new client.
Mark pushes boundaries with two upgrades; the crew overhauls a minivan so it's fit for rock stars and gives the Corvette treatment to a boat.
Shawn pursues the pieces he needs for a big trade; Mark puts his stamp on a kit car; the garage is treated to a surprise visit from Caveman's mother.
Mark and Shawn make progress on a deal; the crew fixes up a jalopy for a race, then upgrades a vintage racecar.
Mark overhauls a 1947 military-style Dodge Power Wagon; Shawn is in the driver's seat when he surveys buyers for a 1960 Plymouth XNR.
The crew weighs an opportunity of a lifetime -- one that entails a great deal of prestige but comes at a big cost.
Dora and Boots hop on Pegaso, the flying horse constellation, for a high-flying adventure to bring home his constellation friends to the Moon before the Sun rises!
For their first birthday, the Super Babies need to team up with Dora, Boots, and you to save all the birthday cakes from the Cake-snatching Bear!
Boots needs a haircut so he can look good for his mommy's birthday picture! Join Dora as she takes Boots for a visit to el Peluquero at the Barbershop!
Team up with Dora and Boots to get Baby Winky back to his family's spaceship before it blasts off on its return flight to the Purple Planet!

It's the Grumpy Old Troll's wedding and everything is all set except he forgot to pick up the rings from his Grandma's House! With Dora's help, we have to get the rings and make it back to the wedding in time!
epi_name: The Grumpy Old Troll Gets Married

epi_desc: Dora's dance class is having a show for all their friends and family. Dora can't wait for her family to see her dance! She needs her dance slippers, but the Delivery Duck delivers scuba flippers instead. The show can't start without the slippers!
It's a big day of "firsts" when Dora and Boots head to the Bike Shop to pink up Boots' very first bike! On the way, we help Benny, Lil' Piggy, and Baby Blue Bird with some very special "firsts" too!
Help Dora and Boots pack up to meet Diego and Baby Jaguar for a night at the Rainforest Campground, and help Dora's friends get set for their trips too.
Let's explore school! Help Dora, her new friend Pepe the Pig, and their class earn 3 gold stars for a Popcorn Party as they explore Music Class, Story Time, and Math Class too!
Dora and Boots, and YOU need to help Little Monster find a costume so he can march in the Halloween Parade!
epi_name: The Tale of the Unicorn King

epi_desc: Dora and Boots return to Enchanted Forest to save it from Owl, who has taken over as king and set up new rules banning scarecrows, elves and fairies from the forest! Dora, Boots, and their forest friends need your help!
Dora, Boots, and King Unicornio leave Enchanted Forest to join Diego in making the lost continent of Atlantis rise by ending an ancient feud between unicorns and dragons!

The Big Red Chicken accidentally turns Boots into a chicken with his magic wand! But when he sneezes the wand flies away and breaks! We have to help them get to the Wand Shop so they can turn Boots back into a monkey!

Swiper was using his NEW super-Swiper-spin to pack all of his favorite things for a sleepover at his Grandma's House but a big wind comes and blows everything away! Swiper needs helps getting his favorite things back!
epi_name: The Big Red Chicken's Magic Wand

epi_desc: When the train to the Big Horse Show breaks down, Dora, Boots, and Pinto the Pony need your help to get there with the ribbons, so Pinto can win his first blue prize ribbon!
Inspired by the story of Don Quixote, Dora and Boots join Rocinante the Horse and Dapple the Donkey to become real knights!
On the way to the new playground, Dora and Boots find out that the Grumpy Old Troll is stuck in a magic hole! The go on a rhyming adventure to Troll Land to help free him!

Dora and Boots walking in the forest and discover a gate leading to the magical Fairytale Land. When they go inside, a witch casts a spell on Boots that causes him to fall asleep. Dora must become a princess in order to wake him up.
It's Dora's cousin Daisy's 15th birthday party, her quinceañera. But the party can't start without Dora and Boots - they need to teach everybody the mambo.
Yo ho ho, Dora and Boots and all of their friends are putting on a pirate show today.
Dora has some really exciting news to tell us: Someone new is joining Dora's family!

Dora's baby brother and sister just love bananas, but they also love stories! So Dora tells them a Super Babies story! The Super Babies have to get their bananas back from that Super Villain Swiper the Fox.

It's a bright, sunny morning, and Dora wants to say hello to her baby brother and sister. But when Dora gets to their room, she sees that the babies have climbed into their baby carriage and are heading downhill!
Abuela gives Dora and Boots a present for Dora's new puppy, but they'll have to watch out for Swiper, who's got a bunch of new swiping tricks up his sleeves.
It's a high-speed, around-the-world adventure as Dora and her cousin Diego chase after Boots, who's being carried off on his giant kite by a mighty wind.
epi_name: Dora and Diego to the Rescue!

epi_desc: Dora and Boots set out to help King Juan el Bobo find his crown so we can all go to his MamÃ¡'s birthday party. Where did the forgetful king put his crown?

Diego has saved animals, but now he's the one who needs to be saved because he accidentally ended up on a cliff when rescuing a vulture and if he falls off the cliff, he gets punctured by a large pile of cacti.
It's summertime, and Dora and Boots are having a blast at the beach. But suddenly, they encounter the strangest sight - a snowman in Summer?
Happy Best Friends Day! Today's a special day for best friends to play together.
Blast into outer space as Dora and Boots set off to bring 5 stranded space creatures back home to the Purple Planet.

Put on your dancing shoes, because Dora needs you to spin, shake wiggle, jump and clap with her as she tries to rescue Swiper the fox, who's been trapped inside a bottle by a mean dancing elf.Â It's gonna take one really big wish to get Swiper out of the bottle.
